Interface IListOfStrings

All Known Implementing Classes:
LinkedListOfStrings
public interface IListOfStrings
ADT (Abstract Data Type) interface defining the contract for a List of Strings.

This interface specifies all public behaviors that any implementation of a List of Strings must provide. The contract is implementation-agnostic: callers depend only on this interface, not on any concrete class.

An empty list is a valid state. All methods must handle the empty list without throwing unexpected exceptions.

    • containsAll

      boolean containsAll(IListOfStrings other)
      Checks whether every element of the given list is also present in this list.

      Returns true vacuously if other is empty, because every element of an empty set is trivially contained in any set.

      Parameters:
      other - the list of strings to check for; must not be null
      Returns:
      true if all elements of other are in this list; false otherwise
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if other is null

    • filterLargerThan

      IListOfStrings filterLargerThan(int maxLength)
      Returns a new list containing only the elements whose length does not exceed the given maximum length.

      Elements with length > maxLength are excluded. The original list is not modified.

      Parameters:
      maxLength - the maximum allowed string length (inclusive)
      Returns:
      a new IListOfStrings with all oversized elements removed
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if maxLength is negative

    • hasDuplicates

      boolean hasDuplicates()
      Checks whether this list contains at least one duplicate element.

      Two elements are considered duplicates if they are equal by String.equals(Object).

      Returns:
      true if any element appears more than once; false otherwise

    • removeDuplicates

      IListOfStrings removeDuplicates()
      Returns a new list with all duplicate elements removed, retaining only the first occurrence of each unique string.

      The original list is not modified. Relative order of first occurrences is preserved.

      Returns:
      a new IListOfStrings with duplicates removed
